    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Rails: get specific attribute from model]]></title>
    <link href="http://tommytcchan.github.com/blog/2013/05/08/rails-get-specific-attribute-from-model/"/>
    <updated>2013-05-08T20:49:00-07:00</updated>
    <id>http://tommytcchan.github.com/blog/2013/05/08/rails-get-specific-attribute-from-model</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I was working getting just the ids from a list of models, and in Rails 3 you can actually use the <code>pluck</code> method for that!</p>

<p>```</p>

<pre><code>shortcuts = Shortcut.where(:software_id =&gt; params[:software_id]).pluck(:id)
</code></pre>

<p>```</p>

<p>This returns:</p>

<p><code>
[58, 59, 60 ...]
</code></p>

<p>awesome!</p>
]]></content>
